Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of computer vision techniques to enhance mobile eye tracking data in order to analyze teachers' attentional processes in the classroom. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on human-computer interaction (cs.HC), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and robotics (cs.RO) as they relate to the analysis of teachers' attentional processes.
